{"block": {"name": "code", "text": "<div style='padding:10px;border:1px solid #d9d9d9;border-radius:10px;background:#fcfcff;line-height:1.45'><p><b>Taylor (1st order): practical task</b></p><p>Compute linear approximation: <code>L(x)=f0+df0*(x-x0)</code>.</p><p>Input: <code>f0 df0 x x0</code>. Output: <code>L(x)</code>.</p><p><b>Посмотреть решение:</b><br><a href='https://github.com/SENATOROVAI/L-BFGS-B-solver-course/blob/main/taylor_first_order_solution.py'>https://github.com/SENATOROVAI/L-BFGS-B-solver-course/blob/main/taylor_first_order_solution.py</a></p></div>", "options": {}, "source": {"code": "import random\n\ndef solve(dataset, **kwargs):\n    vals = [float(v) for v in dataset.strip().split()]\n    f0, df0, x, x0 = vals\n    return '{:.6f}'.format(f0 + df0 * (x - x0))\n\ndef generate(seed=None, **kwargs):\n    rnd = random.Random(seed)\n    tests = []\n    for _ in range(12):\n        f0 = rnd.uniform(-5, 5)\n        df0 = rnd.uniform(-5, 5)\n        x0 = rnd.uniform(-3, 3)\n        x = x0 + rnd.uniform(-1, 1)\n        ds = '{:.6f} {:.6f} {:.6f} {:.6f}\\n'.format(f0, df0, x, x0)\n        tests.append((ds, solve(ds)))\n    return tests\n\ndef check(reply, clue, **kwargs):\n    try:\n        r = float(str(reply).strip())\n        c = float(str(clue).strip())\n        return (1, '') if abs(r - c) <= 1e-5 else (0, 'Wrong answer')\n    except Exception:\n        return (0, 'Bad output format')\n\ndef sample(**kwargs):\n    return ('', '')\n", "execution_time_limit": 2, "execution_memory_limit": 256, "samples_count": 2, "templates_data": "::python3\n::code\n# PSEUDOCODE (First-order Taylor approximation)\n# 1) Read f0, df0, x, x0\n# 2) Compute delta = x - x0\n# 3) Compute L = f0 + df0 * delta\n# 4) Print L with 6 digits after decimal point\n\nf0, df0, x, x0 = map(float, input().split())\nL = f0 + df0 * (x - x0)\nprint('{:.6f}'.format(L))\n", "is_time_limit_scaled": false, "is_memory_limit_scaled": false, "manual_time_limits": [], "manual_memory_limits": [], "test_archive": []}}, "id": "3600001", "has_review": false, "time": "2026-03-06T12:00:00.000Z"}